detaileddescription.para: Copyright 2010 Jay and Han (laughinghan@gmail.com) License, Usage and Readme at http://mathquill.com MathElement is the core Math DOM tree node prototype. Both MathBlock's and MathCommand's descend from it.
Commands and operators, like subscripts, exponents, or fractions. Descendant commands are organized into blocks. May be passed a MathFragment that's being replaced.
Lightweight command without blocks or children.
Children and parent of MathCommand's. Basically partitions all the symbols and operators that descend (in the Math DOM tree) from ancestor operators.
An entity outside the Math DOM tree with one-way pointers (so it's only a "view" of part of the tree, not an actual node/entity in the tree) that delimit a list of symbols and operators.
